				<p><pb facs="#f017"/>18</p>
				<p>given, ^<add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z035" hand="metadata#ESM" place="above" rend="caret">in <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z000" hand="metadata#ESM" rend="single-stroke">some</del> certain cases)</add> even from some Englishmen, than<lb/> from <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z002" hand="metadata#ESM" rend="single-stroke">our</del> <add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z003" hand="metadata#StB" place="above" rend="caret">their</add> own countrymen. ^<add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z004" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">There are hardly five critics in America, and several of them are asleep.</add> <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z005" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">And</del> As for<lb/> patronage, it is the American author who<lb/> now patronizes the country, and not his<lb/> country him. And if at times some<lb/> among them appeal to the people for <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z006" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">a</del> more<lb/> recognition, it is not always with selfish<lb/> motives, but patriotic ones.</p>
				<p>It is true, that but few of <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z007" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">there</del> ^<add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z008" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">them</add><lb/> as yet have evinced that decided originality<lb/> which merits great praise. But that<lb/> graceful <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z009" hand="metadata#ESM" rend="multiple-stroke">author</del> writer, who perhaps of all<lb/> Americans <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z010" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">authors</del> has received ^<add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z011" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">the</add> most plaudits<lb/> from his own country for his productions,--that<lb/> ^<add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z012" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">very popular and amiable</add> writer, however good, ^<add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z013" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">&amp; self-reliant</add> in many things, perhaps<lb/> owes his chief <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z014" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">excellence</del> ^<add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z015" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">reputation</add> to the self-acknowledged<lb/> imitation of a<del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z016" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">n English</del> ^<add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z017" hand="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z017" place="above" rend="caret">foreign</add> model, and to the studied avoidance of all topics but smooth <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z018" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">and </del><lb/><del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z019" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">easy</del> ones. But it is better to fail in originality,<lb/> than to <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z020" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">exceed</del> ^<add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z021" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">succeed</add> in imitation. <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z022" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">And</del> He who has<lb/> never failed ^<add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z023" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">somewhere,</add> that man can not be great. ^<add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z023" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">Failure is the true test of greatness</add>.<lb/> And if it be said, that <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z025" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">continual</del> ^<add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z026" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">continual</add> success is a<lb/> proof that a man <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z027" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">merely</del> ^<add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z028" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">wisely</add> knows his powers,-<lb/>it is only to be added, that, ^<add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z029" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">in that case,</add> he knows them to<lb/> be small. Let us believe it, then, once for all,<lb/> that there is no hope for us in these smooth pleasing<lb/> writers <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z030" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">of "unknown" </del>that know their <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z031" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">pleases.</del> ^<add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z032" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">powers.</add> <del change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z036" hand="metadata#HM" rend="single-stroke">They </del><lb/>^<add change="metadata#StB" facs="iiifmossesmanifest.json-1653993449226#f017_z034" hand="metadata#HM" place="above" rend="caret">Without malice, but to speak the plain fact, they</add> but furnish an appendix to Goldsmith, and other<lb/> English authors. And we want no American<lb/> Goldsmiths, nay, we want no American Miltons.</p>
